  "analysis": "The initial setup is complete. The configuration root directory `$NET_CONF_DIR` is set to `/home/user/network_ops`, and all required subdirectories (baseline/, current/, backups/, patches/, logs/) have been created. Placeholder configuration files `router.conf` have been created in both `baseline/` and `current/` directories. The initial log entry has been written to `logs/patch_application.log`. The current working directory is correctly set to `$NET_CONF_DIR`.",
  "plan": "Now, I will proceed with the main troubleshooting sequence:\n1. Create a gzipped backup of the original `current/router.conf`.\n2. Normalize line endings in `current/router.conf` to LF.\n3. Create a unified-diff patch from the normalized `current/router.conf` to `baseline/router.conf`.\n4. Log the creation of the patch.\n5. Calculate and log file size metrics (original file and patch size) into `logs/metrics.json`.\n6. Log the metrics calculation.\n7. Apply the patch to `current/router.conf`.\n8. Log the patch application.\n9. Verify that `current/router.conf` is now byte-for-byte identical to `baseline/router.conf`.\n10. Log the verification result.",
  "commands": [
